Package gov.usgs.anss.cwbqueryclient

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CWBQuery
    This is a stub of a main() for invoking the EdgeQueryClient class using the project name for this class to be slightly less confusing.
    DCC512Outputer
    This class generates 512 byte mini-seed from the returned blocks from a query.
    DCCOutputer
    This class generates 4096 byte mini-seed from the returned blocks from a query.
    DeriveAny
    This class can take a list of MiniSeed blocks and filter and decimate them to a new list of MiniSeed blocks.
    DeriveLH  
    EdgeQueryClient
    This class is the main class for CWBQuery which allows the user to make queries against all files on a CWB or Edge computer.
    HoldingOutputer
    This outputer just sends the blocks to the TCP/IP based holdings server.
    MSOutputer
    Create a simple miniSEED file from the CWBQuery list of miniSEED blocks.
    MSZOutputer
    This outputs a MiniSEED file and fills any gaps with miniSEED blocks with the fill value (def=0).
    Outputer
    This abstract class is extended by every output class that accepts a list of MiniSEED blocks from CWBQuery and then creates the new output file.
    QueryRing
    This class keeps a buffer of a certain length of in the clear data and satisfies requests from it.
    ReadTimeout
    This class implements a timeout on a socket with a minimum time, if the user does not reset this class before the timeout interval expires, the socket is closed.
    Run
    This class creates a list of contiguous blocks.
    SacOutputer
    Write a SAC file from the CWBQuery list of miniSEED blocks with some options.
    SacPZ
    Create a SAC Poles and zeros file from the MDS given a channel name and unit.
    SacSegmentOutputer
    Take the CWBQuery list of MiniSEED blocks and create a SAC file(s) from each segment with some options.
    UdpChannelDump
    This is a simple client that connects to a UdpChannel service and dumps the contents.
    VMSServer
    This class handle queries from VMS and is now obsolete
    WFDiscMSOutputer
    This writes out WFDISC where the time series remains as miniSEED blocks.
    WFDiscOutputer
    This outputer creates WFDISC files from the CWBQuery list of miniseed blocks.
    ZeroFilledSpan
    This class represent a time series chunk which is zero filled (or filled with user specified value) if data is missing.
